&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="videobox"&gt;
                &lt;iframe width="640" height="390"
                    src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/3-bwXhts8Zg'
                    frameborder='0' webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen
                    allowFullScreen&gt;
                &lt;/iframe&gt;
            &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To do so I followed &lt;a href="https://pythonforundergradengineers.com/how-i-built-this-site-4.html"&gt;the tutorial&lt;/a&gt;. Since some of the materials there are out of date, so I explain a little bit in the following. You could use the plugin &lt;code&gt;liquid_tags.youtube&lt;/code&gt; in &lt;code&gt;pelicanconf.py&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;#pelicanconf.py&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="n"&gt;PLUGINS&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;liquid_tags.youtube&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;And then include the following line in your post &lt;code&gt;second_post.md&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;{% youtube Qq-5frjUfK0 [640] [390] %}
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Notice here the difference between the one in &lt;a href="https://pythonforundergradengineers.com/how-i-built-this-site-4.html"&gt;the tutorial&lt;/a&gt; and the above is that I only write the video id for the youtube video instead of the full https address.&lt;/p&gt;</content></entry></feed>